Most of all, Paclík allegedly interferes with Pelta's connection with the chairman of the Pilsner district football association Roman Berbr, a man with a controversial reputation, who is regarded as a powerful lobbyist behind the scenes, with the ability to influence delegate votes at general meetings.
For Paclík, it is therefore unacceptable that Pelta should hold the position of Chairman.
"With his victory, today's state would be preserved and Czech football would not go ahead at all."
"The support of Berbr, a clever business man, would be twice as bad for football," Paclík emphasized.
