In many places seed crows are regarded as "problem birds": But the highly intelligent animals can no longer be driven out of the cities, according to experts.
Some like it, others want to get rid of it very quickly: crows have been part of the cityscape for centuries, but in many municipalities, local residents are amassing complaints about the dirt and noise of animals.
A remedy against the "problem birds" is not yet in sight.
Experts at the first crow symposium in the East Frisian void said that it was impossible to get seed crows out of the cities.
There, experts from all over Germany discussed possible solutions.
You are looking for alternatives in cities
Nature conservationists also attributed the problems in cities to the rural exodus of the specially protected seed crows: the use of chemicals in agriculture increasingly destroys the traditional habitats.
The hunting, increasing cultivation and falling of typical breeding trees made life difficult for the birds.
Crows are protected.
There are large colonies with more than 600 breeding pairs in the Westphalian Soest, in the northwest among others in Jever, Diepholz and Achim near Bremen as well as in Leer.
