Monti has managed to form a government in less than three days, which is much less time than normal. Meanwhile, Italy is fighting a political and financial crisis that has pushed the cost of debt to an unbearable level.
The new government, led by former Commissioner Monti, must adopt a tough austerity package called for by the Europolitics in order to regain the troubled confidence in Italy.
