Apart from the disputes over fees, the architects agree to the tender.
The urban call for proposals on the 16 gates opens the debate on the importance of Collserola in Barcelona anew.
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the now disappeared Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this administration published its defamation on the promotion of Collserola.
The brochure described the mountain as a huge park in Barcelona city.
He was even compared in numbers with Central Park of New York.
With the fall of the CMB in 1987, the park became, in the eyes of many, the upper limit of Barcelona, because the capital of Catalonia is one of the few that spreads not in the north-south direction, but up (mountains) and down (sea).
The classification of Collserolas as a natural park plays with this idea.
The role model was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wild boar in the role of the yogi bear.
This was the time when the city issued a huge invitation to tender in September, consisting of 16 competitions, for further access gates to Collserola.
There is no doubt that a gate refers to the concept of a park.
