Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in urban planning, regards the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" that carries "some dangers".
Risks arising from the "uncertainty that the design of a public space today entails" following the experience of the 1980s, who had their "swan song" in the forum.
The first fear is one's own limitation to what can be built up.
